overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of their sleep questionnaire
  application, seeking to validate its adherence to the provided Statement of
  Work and detailed specifications. The agent conducted an in-depth analysis,
  pinpointing several critical missing features and areas for improvement.
  Following this review, the agent systematically implemented all identified
  enhancements. Key additions included a 1-10 tiredness severity scale with
  integrated safety warnings, sophisticated detection logic for COMISA (Comorbid
  Insomnia and Sleep Apnea) and Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and a weighted
  scoring system for Excessive Daytime Sleepiness (EDS). The agent also expanded
  the CSV export functionality to encompass all questionnaire data, introduced
  new questions for pain severity and chronic fatigue screening, and
  incorporated sections for medical and mental health history. Furthermore,
  placeholder outbound links to relevant medical and educational resources were
  added to both the interactive and PDF reports, significantly enriching the
  application's utility and user guidance.
